SIMPLE: subornation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subornation
<hw>Sub`or*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>subornation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The act
of suborning; the crime of procuring a person to take such a false oath
as constitutes perjury.</def> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The sin or offense of procuring one to do a criminal
or bad action, as by bribes or persuasion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Foul <qex>subornation</qex> is predominant.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sort of chicanery attending the <qex>subornation</qex> of
managers in the Leibnitz controversy.</q> <rj><qau>De
Quinsey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suborner</ent>⟦br⟧
